6:
Whoa... I'm not sure what I'm looking
at, but it's pretty cool.
9: Hopper, what kind of ad is this?
13:
Oh, that's for Gen1. You know, car
sports.
16:
You call this stuff sports? The cars
are just hitting each other and
exploding.
21:
Sure. You ever heard of extreme
sports? And FYI, bionics are hooked
up to the engine system. They're the
ones pulling the stunts.
23:
They're free to race normally, battle
each other, crash into things, cause
deadly accidents... You name it, they
probably do it.
26:
Lots of betting involved too, by the
way.
30:
I can see why it'd be popular in your
world...
36:
If you're curious, want to help me
with a job?
38:
Noxel actually just gave me
something regarding Gen1...
42:
They want me to do a little probe
into a new racer. Figure out if he's
okay to sponsor.
47:
Yeah, Gen1 regulates its cars AND its
racers.
49:
Can't have any mods be too
high-tech, 'cause then, what's the
point of individual talent, yeah?
68:
I got an autograph AND a
handshake!
72:
You were hanging out as a fan?!
What about the job?
76: Don't worry, I did what I came to do.
80:
Worked a little bit of my magic while
he was distracted by the
handshake. He won't be waking up
until morning.
84:
Wait. You put him under without his
consent?!
88:
Come on, don't be such a spoilsport.
You're starting to sound like Light.
90:
I'm going to do a dive into his
memories. In the meantime, you
keep an eye out!
113:
Hopper, are you all there? Can you
answer me?
117:
Y-yeah... I can. But... what
happened? Why are we here?
120:
You stood up out of nowhere, said
you had to come back, then walked
out without another word.
122:
What happened when you were
looking into his memories?
126:
He didn't have any illegal mods... But
his memories were basically a black
box.
128:
Or rather... he didn't have any
memories. So then the system
redirected back to me...
131:
You know, I've been hearing some
rumors lately—stuff about how
synthetics are becoming more like
people every day.
132:
Thought it was all nonsense, but
now...
136:
The job was to figure out if he was
okay to sponsor, right? You said he
didn't have any illegal mods.
140:
Also, from what I saw of his races,
he's pretty good at his job.
145: Yeah, that's why I'm a fan of his.
149:
I know. You got his autograph,
remember?
154: Yeah, yeah. Just let it go already.
157:
We'll tell the clients that he's clean of
illegal tech and good for
sponsorship. That's all the truth they
need to know.
161:
Yep, you're not lying if you say that
much.
165:
Anything else is outside the terms of
our contract.
167:
Hey, Alk, you going to that
Kaleidoscope thing any time soon?
169:
I'm in the mood for a little bit of
destruction.
173:
Sure, we can make some plans. I'll
call Nimbus, and we can go crazy
like those racers.
177: Yeah. Can't let them hog all the fun.
